1)  ANALYSIS OF MAIN TARGET IMAGE

   ■  Overall there are two separate “towers”:

   A)  Left Tower  
      •  Bottom Layer:  
         – A single long yellow rectangular block spanning the base.  
         – Two vertical orange cylinders side by side resting on this base.  
      •  Middle Layer:  
         – Another yellow rectangular block lying horizontally across the two cylinders.  
         – Two blue cubes side by side on top of that yellow block.  
      •  Top Layer:  
         – A red arch block set above the two blue cubes.  
         – An orange wedge/roof block on very top.

   B)  Right Tower  
      •  Front Row (Base):  
         – Two red arch blocks, placed side by side with arches facing forward.  
         – On top of these arches sit two yellow half‐cylinders, side by side.  
      •  Back Row:  
         – Two green rectangular blocks (shorter) standing directly behind the half‐cylinders.  
         – Two tall yellow rectangular blocks standing behind (or just behind/adjacent to) the green blocks.

2)  REQUIRED BLOCKS FROM THE DICTIONARY

   For left tower:  
      – #7 (Yellow rectangular block) × 2  
      – #9 (Orange cylinder) × 2  
      – #4 (Blue cube) × 2  
      – #1 (Red arch) × 1  
      – #12 (Orange wedge/roof) × 1  

   For right tower:  
      – #1 (Red arch) × 2  (same orientation as the left‐tower arch)  
      – #11 (Yellow half‐cylinder) × 2  
      – #6 (Green rectangular block) × 2  
      – #8 (Tall yellow rectangular block) × 2  

3)  STEP‐BY‐STEP ASSEMBLY ORDER

{
  Step1:  Move block with index 7       (left tower base)  
  Step2:  Move block with index 9       (first orange cylinder)  
  Step3:  Move block with index 9       (second orange cylinder)  
  Step4:  Move block with index 7       (yellow bridging block)  
  Step5:  Move block with index 4       (first blue cube)  
  Step6:  Move block with index 4       (second blue cube)  
  Step7:  Move block with index 1       (red arch on top)  
  Step8:  Move block with index 12      (orange wedge roof)  

  Step9:  Move block with index 1       (first red arch for right tower)  
  Step10: Move block with index 1       (second red arch for right tower)  
  Step11: Move block with index 11      (first yellow half‐cylinder)  
  Step12: Move block with index 11      (second yellow half‐cylinder)  
  Step13: Move block with index 6       (first green rectangular block)  
  Step14: Move block with index 6       (second green rectangular block)  
  Step15: Move block with index 8       (first tall yellow block)  
  Step16: Move block with index 8       (second tall yellow block)  
}
